&lt;p&gt;Veriff is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Director of Sales; Americas &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;to drive revenue, oversee US and LATAM&amp;nbsp; expansion, and manage our US and Latam&amp;nbsp; Sales Team (Enterprise Account Executives). This Leader will drive key decisions within the company&#39;s executive leadership team to develop both short and long term strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that Revenue’s high growth targets are met from new customer acquisition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive key decisions with the company’s executive leadership team to develop both short and long term strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with the largest strategic opportunities, leading executive relationships and helping the team navigate long sales cycles to win new customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and mentor the current sales&amp;nbsp; team, inspiring a cohesive and performance-driven culture and team spirit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring discipline and structure to the sales process to deliver the best possible customer experience throughout the sales cycle, while ensuring accurate and reliable forecasting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in partnership with the Product and Engineering teams to ensure the goal of offering market-leading products and service solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the finance department to implement better metrics to improve revenue forecasting and better utilize resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop best practices that enable the organization to more rapidly scale to deliver on revenue targets and support KPIs for growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular alignment with internal stakeholders to continue to drive significant impact across all markets and grow the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have extensive sales hunter experience, specializing in serving multinational enterprise customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with sales forecasting and metrics, coaching and driving sales methodologies and processes (mastery of MEDDICC is a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven capability to lead and deliver significant growth, through revenue team expansion and/or improved efficiencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to articulate the distinct aspects of services and products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in defining processes, KPIs, and guidance for teams to follow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relentless drive to achieve results, strong willed, motivating and cool under pressure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Metrics driven &amp;amp; process oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are an inspirational and hands-on leader with 10+ years working in the US, with demonstrated experience in leading senior sales contributors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have the ability to pick up on complex IDV discussions in order to assist your team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team-oriented. Focused on what’s right for the customer , not what’s right for the individual or function; ability to build deep relationships and earn the respect of other teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong, decisive and action-oriented leadership style; ability to make, communicate, and take accountability for timely decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creates strong morale, good spirit in his/her team and brings fun to the workplace; shares wins and successes; fosters open dialogue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Veriff?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are the preferred identity verification platform partner for the world’s most innovative growth-driven organizations helping conveniently verify and safeguard users anywhere in the world. We support the broadest number of identity documents from nearly every country and territory in the world - and this is continually increasing! With a diverse team in the United States, United Kingdom, Spain, Brazil, and Estonia, as well as r

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fraud Countermeasure Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Veriff, our Product team builds the solution to solve the online identity crisis. We focus on creating scalable technology that looks to the future while keeping innovation at our core.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the Fraud Group, we are tackling online fraud with innovation and determination, constantly evolving to stay ahead of emerging threats. As part of our Fraud Countermeasure team, you will play a pivotal role in keeping fraudsters at bay while safeguarding the interests of our customers. If you’re someone who thrives in fast-paced environments and enjoys searching for patterns in large datasets, this might be the perfect opportunity for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;ll help us protect honest people online by:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigating and analyzing cases of suspected fraud affecting Veriff’s customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring, inspecting, and validating fraud strategy outcomes to ensure they meet compliance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing new countermeasures and strategies to address emerging fraud patterns while minimizing false positives and negatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with internal and external stakeholders to communicate findings, propose improvements, and ensure product readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluating risk scenarios, identifying system vulnerabilities, and suggesting corrective actions to prevent fraud.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working cross-functionally to improve fraud detection processes and enhance the overall quality of our fraud products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You might be the right person for the job if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3 years of experience in fraud investigation, risk analysis, or AML/KYC/compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to identify patterns and trends in large datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in data analysis tools and techniques (SQL,&amp;nbsp; Tableau or Looker).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A solid understanding of risk assessment, able to predict potential fraud scenarios and propose effective solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in developing and implementing fraud detection strategies and countermeasures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration skills to work effectively with cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to think critically, identify system vulnerabilities, and propose corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and a thorough understanding of fraud methodologies and emerging trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in evaluating risk scenarios and making data-driven recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivation, a high degree of curiosity and autonomy, and the ability to adapt in a dynamic and fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to stay up-to-date with the latest fraud detection technologies and techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; USA (Remote)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Why Veriff?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are the preferred identity verification platform partner for the world’s most innovative growth-driven organizations helping conveniently verify and safeguard users anywhere in the world. We support the broadest number of identity documents from nearly every country and territory in the world - and this is continually increasing! With a diverse team and offices in the United States, United Kingdom, Spain, and Estonia, as well as robust backing and funding from investors including Accel, Alkeon, IVP, Tiger Capital, and Y Combinator, we’re dedicated to helping businesses and individuals build a safer and more secure world. We strive to be the benchmark

&lt;div class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;239&quot; data-end=&quot;500&quot;&gt;In Veriff’s Fraud Platform team, we’re tackling the online fraud challenge in a scalable way — deploying excellence to stay ahead of attackers and protect trust online. It’s a dynamic, high-stakes space where speed, precision, and innovation matter every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fraud Countermeasure Team Lead drives the tactical defense layer of Veriff’s Fraud Platform. By fusing threat intel, behavioral analytics, and real-time signals, the Countermeasures team uncovers new attack patterns, prioritises them by business impact, and ships detection logic that blocks fraud within hours. You will manage a team of fraud experts, own the attack-backlog roadmap, and ensure every countermeasure maximises protection while preserving user experience, speed, and trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll help us protect honest people online by:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, grow, and develop a Fraud Countermeasures team that ships high-impact fraud rules at pace by nurturing a team culture of accountability, experimentation, and cross-functional collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate raw threat intel into a focused detection strategy, aligning the team’s backlog with the Fraud Platform’s north-star metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end delivery—plan sprints, remove blockers, and help team ship countermeasures in hours, not weeks, while communicating crisp updates to execs and the wider company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion tooling and process upgrades—automate intel ingestion, detection testing, and rule deployment—so the team scales faster than the fraud landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product, data science, and engineering stakeholders to craft a long-term vision for proactive detection and inspire the team to chase it independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to Veriff’s global fraud risk posture reinforcement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a red-team mindset: treat every missed fraud case as a controlled breach, and drive cross-functional squads to hunt, replicate, and shut down attacks faster than they can scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support career growth, feedback culture, and skill development in alignment with our internal product management principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executing orders of a direct manager or his/her substitute employee and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;performing other unforeseen tasks as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are the right future Veriffian for the job if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years leading operations team fighting online fraud at scale in fintech, identity, or similar domains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SQL fluency; you can turn raw data into attack stories and metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to build, scale, retain, and drive strong operations teams with a clear sense of purpose and identity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strategic mindset and proven ability to align team efforts with measurable business impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and stakeholder management skills, enabling alignment across technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for mentoring and creating inclusive, high-performing team cultures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You approach complexity with curiosity and tenacity, thrive on uncovering root causes, and seek practical, sustainable solutions to high-impact problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A mindset geared towards innovation and product discovery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;d be awesome for the role if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Red-team or threat-intel background.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with ML-driven systems and the ability to partner fluently with data scientists and ML engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in implementing new tools or technologies

